HEADWORD: firepower
<hw>firepower</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(military)</fld>
<def>The relative capacity for delivering weapons fire on a target;
<as>as, the battleship has more <ex>firepower</ex> than a
cruiser</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>[figurative]</mark> <def>A measure of the resources
available to a group which allows them to achieve their objectives;
capacity for action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fireproof</ent>⟦br⟧
